1
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja,
 
Yes dear viewers,

2
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
dema mirov dixwaze Efrînê lêkolîn bike,
 
when one wants to research Afrin,

3
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,000
mirov vedigere dîroka bi hezar sala.
 
one goes back to a history of thousands of years.

4
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Dîroka Hûriyan û Kûtiyan.
 
The history of Hurrians and Gutians.

5
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Ev çiya bi navê Kûtiya tê naskirin.
 
This mountain is known by the name of Gutians.

6
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Gundek li vir ava bûye, jê re dibêjin gundê Berkaşê.
 
A village was built here, it's called the village of
Berkash.

7
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Ev gund jî girêdayî navçeya Bilbilê ye.
 
This village is also connected to the Bilbil district.

8
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Dê ka em herin jî em vî gundî nas bikin.
 
Let's go now and get to know this village.

9
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Gundê Berkaşê.
 
The village of Berkash.

10
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja,
 
Yes dear viewers,

11
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,000
naha jî em li gundê Berkaşê ne.
 
now we are in the village of Berkash.

12
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Kûşkarek li vir e, me go em silavek lê bikin ev kûşkar.
 
There's a cobbler here, we said let's greet this cobbler.

13
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Merheba.
 
Hello.

14
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Merheba ji te re hevalê delal,
 
Hello to you dear friend,

15
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,000
ser çava ser seran, tu bi xêr hatî.
 
welcome, you brought joy.

16
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Tu bi xêr hatî.
 
Welcome.

17
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Qewet be.
 
More power to you.

18
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Xwedê te xweş bike. Ser çava, ser seran. Kerem ke rûnê.
 
May God make you well. Welcome. Please, sit down.

19
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Sax bî. Tu xweş bî.
 
How are you?

20
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Sax bî. Tu xweş bî.
 
Thank you. Be well.

21
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Tu kûşkar e?
 
You're a cobbler?

22
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Em kûşkar in heval.
 
We are cobblers, friend.

23
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Tu çend sal e kûşkar e?
 
How many years have you been a cobbler?

24
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Welleh teqriben sî sal, sî û du-sê sal e.
 
By God, approximately thirty years, thirty-two or three
years.

25
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Elmuhîm ji heftê û şeşan da ez vî karî dikim.
 
Anyway, I've been doing this job since seventy-six.

26
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Îşte qeçike em xwe pê debare dikin.
 
Well, we make a small living with it.

27
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Em dest pê bikin te nas bikin ewînce.
 
Let's start by getting to know you first.

28
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Heval navê min, me'na eşîreta min Emiş e.
 
Friend, my name, I mean my tribe is Emiş.

29
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Navê te yê rastî ye ev?
 
Is this your real name?

30
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Navê min ê rastî Ehmed e.
 
My real name is Ehmed.

31
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Çima gundî te ra dibêjin te ra Emiş?
 
Why do the villagers call you Emiş?

32
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Ê heval îşte, tiştên biçûk henek û tişt bike...
 
Well friend, small things like doing jokes and things...

33
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,000
komedî bike ku heta milet ji te hez bike.
 
doing comedy so that people like you.

34
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Şano kin ev e ku wer e,
 
They made plays like this,

35
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,000
em bi şuxilê qeçkê xwe bi xwe debare dikin.
 
we make a small living with this work.

36
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Çend zarokên te hene?
 
How many children do you have?

37
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Destê te maç dikin dudû ne.
 
They kiss your hand, there are two.

38
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Yek...
 
One...

39
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Mihemed e, yek jî Entoy e.
 
is Mihemed, the other is Ento.

40
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Ne zalim e dikê, elmuhîm destê te maç dikin.
 
He says don't be cruel, anyway they kiss your hand.

41
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Xwedê ji te re bihêle.
 
May God spare them for you.

42
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Xwedê te bihêle.
 
May God spare you.

43
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Ma ne me go were ji me ra bi şuxilekî emîl bixebite?
 
Didn't we say come and work for us as an agent?

44
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Yahu karê emaletê ez nakarim bikim.
 
Oh man, I can't do agent work.

45
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Çima te nedikir ev kar? Me digot were emîliyê ji me re bike,
ji Erdogan re bike.
 
Why couldn't you do this work? We said come do agent work
for us, for Erdogan.

46
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Yaw... way way way way way...
 
Oh man... wow wow wow wow wow...

47
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:28,000
bav û kalê min ketine heştê, heştê û sê salan e...
 
my fathers and grandfathers reached eighty, eighty-three
years...

48
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Ne ji min re dibe gawirek...
 
It is not said of me that I'm an infidel...

49
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Ne ji min re dibe misilmanek!
 
It is not said of me that I'm a Muslim!

50
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Ez ê naha rabim ji te û Erdogan re emaletiyê bikim?
 
Will I now get up and do agent work for you and Erdogan?

51
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Deqîqe... deqîqe... deqîqe...
 
Wait a minute... wait a minute... wait a minute...

52
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja... me xwest em bi destpêkê da şanoyekî
pêşkêş bikin.
 
Yes dear viewers... we wanted to present a play at the
beginning.

53
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Bi rastî jî ev ne kûşkar e...
 
Actually, he is not a cobbler...

54
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Karê wî ne kûşkar e.
 
His job is not a cobbler.

55
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Lê di vê şanogeriyê de kûşkar e.
 
But in this play, he is a cobbler.

56
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Careke din, qewet be jê re.
 
Once again, more power to him.

57
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Sax bî... saeta we xweş...
 
Thank you... have a good time...

58
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Ema di destpêkê de we şanoyek çêkir ji me ra.
 
But at the beginning, you put on a play for us.

59
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Her tim xweş bî û xweşiya vî miletî tebayî be heval.
 
Always be well and may the joy of this nation be eternal,
friend.

60
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Eşîreta te, navê te yê gund Emiş e, tu çima Emiş î?
 
Your tribe, your village name is Emiş, why are you Emiş?

61
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Îşte, bi henekan û zarokan her tişt îşte gerek em pê
bilîzin.
 
Well, with jokes and kids, everything, well, we have to play
with it.

62
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Îşte navê min Ehmed e ji bo sebebê henekên mirovên xwe re,
 
Well, my name is Ehmed, because of making jokes with my
people,

63
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
nav lê kirin înxîfad, li xwe ne me'ne qemiş e.
 
they called me "inxifad" (shrunken), meaning it is "qemiş"
(wrinkled).

64
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Ne şano ye ne... Na am bi rastî de ne...
 
Not a play... No, we are in reality...

65
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Temam em di rastiyê de ne.
 
Okay, we are in reality.

66
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Temam em bavên... Navê te Ehmed e.
 
Okay, let's say... Your name is Ehmed.

67
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
Ser çavan... apê Ehmed.
 
You're welcome... uncle Ehmed.

68
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Em navê te yê gundî bizanibin?
 
Can we know your village name?

69
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Navê min Menan Osman e. Mam Uye ji gundê Berkaşê me.
 
My name is Menan Osman. I'm Uncle Uye from the village of
Berkash.

70
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Welleh ser çavan, apê Menan.
 
By God, you're welcome, uncle Menan.

71
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Te digo êlê mehmuyo,
 
You would say "êle mehmuyo",

72
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
te teqalîda xwe winda dikir.
 
you were losing your traits.

73
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Îla bi lehçeya ereba dipeyivî yan... yaw ev Kurd e...
 
You would only speak in the Arabic dialect or... oh man,
this is a Kurd...

74
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Welleh ez Kurdê qehreman im, navê min Menan e.
 
By God, I am a heroic Kurd, my name is Menan.

75
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Pir xweş bû, bi rastî ev jî skeçekî xweş bû di vê şanoyê de.
 
It was really nice, truly this was also a nice sketch in
this play.

76
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Tu xweş bî... hevalê şerîf tu bi kuderê ra emr dikî, ez di
xizmeta te de me.
 
May you be well... noble friend, wherever you command, I am
at your service.

77
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Em birayê hev in, em hevalên hev in. Xwedê bide we afiyet...
Te pîroz be... sax bî.
 
We are brothers, we are friends. May God give you health...
Congratulations... be well.

78
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Naha em dibêjin qala şanoyê bikin...
 
Now we say let's talk about the play...

79
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Apê Ehmed.
 
Uncle Ehmed.

80
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Te di kîjan salê de û di kîjan demê de dest bi şanoyê kir?
 
Go ahead.

81
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Te di kîjan salê de û di kîjan demê de dest bi şanoyê kir?
 
In what year and what time did you start doing plays?

82
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Heval salên nodî, nod û yekê, nod û duduyan, nod û sêsiyan,
nod û çaran,
 
Friend, the nineties, ninety-one, ninety-two, ninety-three,
ninety-four,

83
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
heta niha nod û pêncan, em negihiştin armanca xwe.
 
up to ninety-five now, we didn't reach our goal.

84
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Lê ew nû fîhes... emniyeta dewlet şêdan,
 
But then there was a sense... the security of the mad state,

85
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,000
hevalên ku xwe berbad nedikirin.
 
the friends who wouldn't ruin themselves.

86
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Sirûc û qat, ewên îşkence û we zahmetiyê borandin...
 
Sirens and floors, the ones who endured the torture and
hardship...

87
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:11,000
fihlen zehmetî dîtin partiya me xweş.
 
actually faced difficulties, good for our party.

88
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:15,000
Bi rastî partiya welatparêz a demokrat e.
 
Truly it is a patriotic and democratic party.

89
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Sekineke wê nedît, ku kesekî digot em ê we îşkence bikin û
helak bikin.
 
It didn't see a stop, that anyone said we will torture you
and destroy you.

90
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Di salên nod û pêncan de me mesrehîyek derxist.
 
In the year ninety-five we put out a play.

91
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Naha em bêjin te di kîjan komê de bûyî?
 
Now let's say, in which group were you?

92
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Heval koma Berxwedan bû, koma Agirî bû.
 
Friend, it was the Berxwedan group, it was the Agirî group.

93
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Elmihîm vana komên ha herdik bûn. Kî derxist pêşî? Koma
Berxwedan bû.
 
Anyway, these were the groups, both of them. Who brought it
forward first? It was the Berxwedan group.

94
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Yanî ev di wan deman de Koma Agirî ya zekî bû, Koma...
 
So in those times it was the smart Agirî group, the group...

95
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Erê... heval, ev in. Koma Agirî jî hebû her kîşkê navekî
komekê ya xwe li xwe danîbû heval.
 
Yes... friend, these. There was also the Agirî group, every
person gave a group name to themselves, friend.

96
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Dewê da tenzîmat kêm bûn.
 
At that time organizations were lacking.

97
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Di her demê da elhemdulîlah, tenzîmat rast bûn û ketin nav
qalikê xwe.
 
In every time, thank God, the organizations became real and
fell into their shell.

98
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Çi kom û çi hunermend û çi jî her karek tê kirin, îla bi
nîzamekî.
 
Whether a group or an artist or any work being done, it's
only with a system.

99
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Di vî nîzamî de alhemdulîlah em dikişînin xêrê.
 
In this system, thank God, we are suffering for the good.

100
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Wê demê wek eşwayî bû, em her kesekî karek bi destê xwe
dikir.
 
At that time it was like random, we each did a work with our
own hands.

101
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Apê Ehmed, di şanoyê de karê te kûşkar bû?
 
Uncle Ehmed, in the play your job was a cobbler?

102
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Karê min kûşkar bû.
 
My job was a cobbler.

103
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
We kîderê şano çêdikirin... tu bi kîderê pêşkêş dikir?
 
Where did you do plays... where did you present it?

104
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Heval, ez di eydiyên Newrozê de li her derekê ku koma
mesrehiye hebû em hazir bûn heval.
 
Friend, during the Newroz holidays, wherever there was a
theater group, we were ready, friend.

105
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Di nav seyrangehê bû... li ber kelê bû...
 
It was in the park... it was in front of the castle...

106
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,000
li Çiyayê Cindirîsê li ser telê bû...
 
it was on the Cindires mountain on the hill...

107
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:26,000
heval li her derekê ku dixwestin di van çar salan de em
amade bûn, sînga me ji partiyê re vekirî bû.
 
friend, wherever they wanted in those four years we were
ready, our chests were open to the party.

108
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Yanî li kuderê ba we ev karê xwe dikir?
 
So wherever it was, you did your work?

109
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Em hazir bûn... erê heval.
 
We were ready... yes friend.

110
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Ê hûn çend kes bûn di wê demê de?
 
Well, how many of you were there at that time?

111
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Welleh heval, kes pir bûn taqrîben mesrehîya me dor sed, sed
û sî, sed û çil kes bûn.
 
By God friend, there were many people, approximately our
play was around a hundred, a hundred and thirty, a hundred
and forty people.

112
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,000
Sed û çil kes?
 
A hundred and forty people?

113
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Erê! Hemî jî...
 
Yes! All of them...

114
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Ev kom e, bi giştî?
 
Is this the group, in total?

115
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,000
Ê kom e, mesrehiye ne tenê kom e.
 
The group, the theater is not just the group.

116
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:44,000
Ê bazdanên... ê boçke bin... belkî e bazdanê bîst kes dibin.
 
The runners... would be... maybe the runners would be twenty
people.

117
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Ji qîzan, ji xortan bîst kes bûn.
 
From girls, from youths there were twenty people.

118
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Yanî komeke ceddî bû mesrehiye, ev dîl bû yanî.
 
So it was a serious theater group, this was the heart, I
mean.

119
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Te di şanoyê de aynen bi vî rengî we tişt dikir?
 
Did you do things exactly in this style in the play?

120
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Bi vî rengî me çêdikir heval, teb'en milet hebû ye, hevalên
me hebû,
 
We did it in this style friend, of course there were people,
we had friends,

121
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:59,000
em wisa li ser pêşerojan diketin, karên siyasî di nav da
hebû.
 
we used to fall upon the future like this, there were
political activities involved.

122
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Opozîsyon da hebû... her karek hebû wisa...
 
There was opposition involved... whatever job there was, it
was like this.

123
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Em bêjin naha na bi xwe te rolek tenê hebû an rola te
guherî?
 
Let's say now, did you have only one role yourself or did
your role change?

124
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Na ez rola min ne tenê bû, yanî pêwîst e tiştekî şêrîn be
milet guhdar ke.
 
No, my role was not just one, meaning it's necessary for it
to be a bit sweet so people would listen.

125
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Lewra ji destpêka partiya me da xebatên me bi her rengî
hebû,
 
Because since the beginning of our party, our activities
were in every color,

126
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:16,000
ku heta naha em gihiştin vê merheleyê, çekdariyê û
elhemdulillah me çavê dijmin şikand.
 
until now we reached this stage, armed struggle and thank
God we broke the enemy's eye.

127
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:20,000
Yanî di dorên te de pirs... tu kûşkar bûyî aynen bi vî rengî
te...
 
So questions about your roles... you were a cobbler exactly
in this style...

128
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Temam, yekî dî jî hebû, wekî hevalê Mennan îxanet dikir,
wekî wî eskerê... ecem bû... yan polîsekî Kemalîzmê ye.
 
Okay, there was another one, betraying like comrade Mennan,
like that soldier... he was an Iranian... or a Kemalist
policeman.

129
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Dihatin kerameta Kurda îxanetê bikin.
 
They came to betray the dignity of the Kurds.

130
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Yanî wê şanoyê li ser wê yekê bû?
 
I mean that play was about that?

131
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,000
Holê li ser wê esasê jî me berxwe da... me digot berxwedan
jiyan e.
 
Yes, on that basis we also resisted... we used to say
resistance is life.

132
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Navê wê çi bû? Vê komê...
 
What was its name? This group...

133
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,000
Navê xwe... Berxwedan bû.
 
Its name... was Resistance.

134
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Ji kuderê bû?
 
Where was it from?

135
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Ji Şêxurze bû...
 
It was from Şêxurze...

136
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:48,000
Pir kes hebûn... wele pir kes tên bîra min... li Şêx el-Dîn
ji Mihemed... ji Serincikê bû.
 
There were many people... by God many people come to mind...
in Şêx el-Dîn from Mihemed... from Serincik.

137
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Navê wî nayê bîra min, Muxtar... gundekî gelek kesên me yên
komê hebûn, yanî em berxwe didan.
 
I can't remember his name, Muxtar... there were many people
from a village in our group, meaning we were resisting.

138
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Ê naha em bêjin wê demê de pir zehmetî dikişand ser şanoyê?
 
Well now let's say at that time you faced a lot of
difficulties doing theater?

139
00:07:54,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Heval, zehmetî pir bûn. Hevalêkî me hebû, Ebû Selam bû,
çiqas ji dest wan reviya bî...
 
Friend, there were many difficulties. We had a friend named
Abu Salam, he ran away from them so much...

140
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:04,000
pîxwaz di gundê Şikya... Heta me ji destê wan xilas kir, em
bi xwe hingî gelek xirabtir bûn.
 
barefoot in the village of Şikya... Until we rescued him
